column5: Got a chance yesterday to try some surf fishing down in Florida! Cold front had the fish a little tight lipped but I managed to catch my first Ladyfish! Also got to use a feature that I don't often on my Navionics app on my iPhone to check on the Tides, pretty cool!
Nice going David. Looks like the weather is going to improve for you.

8 degrees? those florida folks must think you are crazy fishing in that kind of cold lol ocean fishing is just a different beast all together. Id like to try surf fishing some time. I have a bunch of buddies that do it in Brisbane Australia.
How come you blacked out the back ground ? HAHAHAHAHA  Nice going David.
Dave, ladyfish are awesome!   Poor mans tarpon     I never mind when those things tug at the other end of the line.  Usually go airborne as well
I guess they call it a Ladyfish because of all the shiny bling .... ? cool fish !!!
Very cool , but be careful you can fall in love with ocean fishing and soon you will have another type of fishing to spend money on. Art
Bass fishing will never be the same
No, bass fishing will always be #1 but I love all kinds of fishing!!!!
Enjoy and good luck with the rest of the time there and catching more fish!  Keep the pic's coming for those of us waiting on ice...
